cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.AL, cs.PF 

This paper deals with scheduling data flows in datacenter networks, which is a topic that falls under the categories of network optimization (cs.NI), distributed computing (cs.DC), algorithms (cs.DS, cs.AL), and performance analysis (cs.PF). The paper specifically focuses on coflow scheduling, which is a relatively new concept in network optimization, and hence, it is likely to be categorized under cs.NI. However, the paper also presents approximation algorithms and interval-indexed linear programs, which are topics that are commonly studied in the algorithms and performance analysis communities, respectively. Therefore, it is also likely to be categorized under cs.AL and cs.PF. Finally, the paper deals with scheduling large-scale computations in datacenters, which is a topic that is relevant to distributed computing, and hence, it is also likely to be categorized under cs.DC.
